A table of the data. There are
three columns, "Brand", "Type", and "Calories". "Type" is the
Explanatory variable, and "Calories" is the Response variable. Some example data:
    Brand 1, Beef, 186;
    Brand 2, Poultry, 129;
    Brand 3, Beef, 181;
    Brand 4, Meat, 183;
    ... (abbreviated) ...
    Brand 54, Poultry, 144
